<subSubSection pageId="105" pageNumber="106" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1438,596,2014]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,541,1678,1704]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Distribution and habitat:—</emphasis>
From 4°29’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[694,788,1678,1704]" degrees="17" direction="south" minutes="50" orientation="latitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="-17.833334">17°50’S</geoCoordinate>
and 62°53’– 
<geoCoordinate box="[939,1047,1678,1704]" degrees="73" direction="west" minutes="35" orientation="longitude" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" precision="925" value="-73.583336">73°35’W</geoCoordinate>
in the western Amazon region in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,226,1717,1743]" name="Brazil" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[237,293,1717,1743]" name="Peru" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[355,441,1717,1743]" name="Bolivia" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
at a mean elevation of 312(150–950) m in lowland rainforest (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1265,1717,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="104.[151,255,1873,1896]" captionTargetBox="[164,1410,848,1856]" captionTargetId="figure@104.[151,1436,828,1873]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="FIGURE 28. Distribution maps of Geonoma monospatha, G. mooreana, G. multisecta, and G. occidentalis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3538418" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3538418/files/figure.png" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1438,596,2014]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,446,1756,1782]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Taxonomic notes:—</emphasis>
This taxon was treated as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barbosa Rodrigues" authorityYear="1879" box="[885,1143,1756,1782]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brevispatha">
<emphasis box="[885,1143,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Geonoma brevispatha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson, A." box="[1186,1401,1756,1782]" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="1 - 362" refId="ref122671" refString="Henderson, A. (1995) Palms of the Amazon, Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 1 - 362." title="Palms of the Amazon" type="book chapter" year="1995">Henderson (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. In the present study, this name is treated as an excluded name, and the taxon to which Henderson was referring is called 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Henderson" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Wendland ex Drude" box="[228,685,1833,1859]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Geonoma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="pohliana" subSpecies="weddelliana">
<emphasis box="[228,453,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Geonoma pohliana</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis box="[542,685,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">weddelliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The similarity between the two taxa is superficial and there are many differences between them, notably in the prophylls (not available to 
<bibRefCitation author="Henderson, A." box="[1022,1224,1872,1898]" journalOrPublisher="Oxford University Press, New York" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" pagination="1 - 362" refId="ref122671" refString="Henderson, A. (1995) Palms of the Amazon, Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 1 - 362." title="Palms of the Amazon" type="book chapter" year="1995">Henderson, 1995</bibRefCitation>
) and in the fruits.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="105.[151,1438,596,2014]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,504,1910,1936]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Subspecific variation:—</emphasis>
Two traits vary within this species (stem branching, stem 
<typeStatus box="[1217,1272,1910,1936]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">type</typeStatus>
). There is no geographic disjunction—the gap in 
<collectingCountry box="[571,657,1949,1975]" name="Bolivia" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
is likely to be an artifact of insufficient collecting. There are three outlying specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[449,520,1988,2014]" name="Brazil" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[536,597,1988,2014]" country="Brazil" name="Acre" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Acre</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[609,725,1988,2014]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Rondônia</collectingRegion>
) and 
<collectingCountry box="[790,844,1988,2014]" name="Peru" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[860,945,1988,2014]" country="Peru" name="Loreto" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Loreto</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
